<longDescription>The `client-sessions`, `cookie-session` or `express-session` library sets the `path` attribute on the session cookie to the root or doesn't set `path` attribute (default value is root). If the application is hosted beneath a subdirectory and the cookie is copied to the root, then applications in other subdirectories will have access to this cookie. If any of these applications become compromised, the cookie of the victim site can be stolen from this application.</longDescription>
